        body: "The Skechers Go Golf Pro 5 is the proof that you do not need to spend $200 for a comfortable walking shoe. At $85, it is lighter and more cushioned than shoes costing twice as much — comfortable from the first step with zero break-in needed.\n\nThe Skechers memory foam insole is the most immediately comfortable insole in our test. It molds to your foot shape within the first few holes and provides genuine cushioning on hard cart paths and firm fairways. The shoe weighs under 10 oz, which makes it the lightest option in this comparison.\n\nThe tradeoff: comfort fades faster than the premium options. By hole 14-15, the memory foam compresses and support decreases. The FootJoy and ECCO both maintain their cushioning longer. For 9-hole rounds or golfers who ride part of the time, this is not an issue. For frequent 18-hole walkers on hilly courses, the Flex XP holds up better over a full round.\n\nThe other limitation: no waterproofing. The Skechers performs well in dry and dewy conditions but soaks through in rain. If you play in wet climates, add $35 for the FootJoy Flex XP waterproof instead.",
