        h2: 'Step 2: Learn the Grip — The Only Fundamental That Matters First',
        body: 'A bad grip causes almost every beginner mistake: slice, fat shots, weak impact. The neutral grip: hold the club in your lead hand fingers (not the palm), both thumbs point down the shaft, see 2.5 knuckles on your lead hand at address. A $15 grip trainer builds this in 2 weeks. This single change fixes more problems than any other beginner investment.',
