    ogImage: 'https://www.cubicalgolfer.com/images/thumbnails/quiet-simulator-thumb.webp',
    thumbnail: '/images/thumbnails/quiet-simulator-thumb.webp',
    words: '1,800',
    category: 'indoor-golf',
    pageType: 'tutorial',
    tag: 'SETUP GUIDE',
    emoji: '🔇',
    datePublished: '2026-05-17',
    dateModified: '2026-05-14',
    title: 'Quiet Golf Simulator Setup',
    titleDisplay: 'How to Build a Quiet Golf Simulator (Apartment & Condo Friendly)',
    description: 'How to build a quiet golf simulator for apartments and condos. Sound dampening, quiet mats, foam balls, and the gear that keeps neighbors happy.',
    excerpt: 'Your neighbors do not want to hear you hitting golf balls at 9 PM. Here is how to build a simulator setup that keeps the noise under 50 dB.',
    bottomLine: 'A quality hitting mat + impact screen (not a net) + sound dampening panels reduce simulator noise to conversation level. Foam balls eliminate noise entirely for late-night practice.',
    intro: `Noise is the #1 reason apartment golfers do not buy a simulator. The crack of a real ball hitting a net at 9 PM will get you a noise complaint. But with the right equipment and setup, you can practice indoors at any hour without disturbing anyone. We measured decibel levels for every component.`,
    toc: ['Noise Sources and Levels', 'Quiet Hitting Mats', 'Screens vs Nets for Noise', 'Sound Dampening', 'Foam Ball Practice', 'Complete Quiet Setup'],
