    title: 'Projector Distance Calculator',
    titleDisplay: 'Golf Simulator Projector Distance Calculator — Find Your Throw Ratio',
    description: 'Golf simulator projector distance calculator. Enter your room depth and screen size to find the right throw ratio and projector model for your setup.',
    excerpt: 'Enter your room dimensions and screen size — we calculate the throw ratio and recommend the right projector.',
    bottomLine: 'Most garage simulators need a short-throw projector (0.5-0.8 throw ratio) because standard projectors require 10+ feet of throw distance most rooms do not have.',
    intro: `Your projector needs to sit a specific distance from the screen to fill it with the right image size. Too close and the image overflows. Too far and the image is too small. This calculator tells you exactly which projector type fits your room.`,
    toc: ['What Is Throw Ratio', 'Calculator', 'Recommended Projectors', 'Mounting Options'],
    updateLog: [{ date: '2026-05-17', note: 'Initial publication' }],
    whoFor: ['Simulator builders choosing a projector', 'Anyone confused by throw ratios'],
    whoSkip: ['Net-only setups (no projector needed)'],
    comparisonTable: {
      caption: 'Projector Types by Throw Ratio',
      headers: ['Type', 'Best For', 'Price', 'Throw Ratio'],
      rows: [
        { affiliateKey: 'garmin-approach-r10', name: 'Ultra Short Throw', bestFor: 'Small rooms', price: '~$1,500+', feature1: '0.2-0.4', feature2: '1-3 ft from screen', badge: 'SMALLEST ROOMS' },
        { affiliateKey: 'garmin-approach-r10', name: 'Short Throw', bestFor: 'Most garages', price: '~$500-$1,000', feature1: '0.5-0.8', feature2: '4-6 ft from screen', badge: 'BEST VALUE', winner: true },
        { affiliateKey: 'garmin-approach-r10', name: 'Standard', bestFor: 'Large rooms', price: '~$300-$600', feature1: '1.0-2.0', feature2: '10-15 ft from screen' },
      ],
    },
    sections: [
      { h2: 'What Is Throw Ratio and Why It Matters', body: '<p>Throw ratio = distance from projector to screen / screen width. A throw ratio of 0.5 means the projector sits at 50% of the screen width. For a 10-foot wide screen, a 0.5 throw ratio projector sits 5 feet away.</p><p>Most garage simulators use 8-10 foot wide screens. Standard projectors need 10-15 feet of distance — more depth than most garages have after accounting for the hitting area. That is why short-throw projectors (0.5-0.8 ratio) are the standard for golf simulators.</p>' },
      { h2: 'Quick Reference Table', body: '<table class="cmp-table"><thead><tr><th>Screen Width</th><th>Short Throw (0.5)</th><th>Short Throw (0.8)</th><th>Standard (1.5)</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>8 ft</td><td>4 ft</td><td>6.4 ft</td><td>12 ft</td></tr><tr><td>9 ft</td><td>4.5 ft</td><td>7.2 ft</td><td>13.5 ft</td></tr><tr><td>10 ft</td><td>5 ft</td><td>8 ft</td><td>15 ft</td></tr><tr><td>12 ft</td><td>6 ft</td><td>9.6 ft</td><td>18 ft</td></tr></tbody></table><p>If your room is under 12 feet deep after the hitting area, you need a short-throw projector. See our <a href="/best-golf-simulator-projectors/">projector buying guide</a> for specific models.</p>' },
      { h2: 'Our Recommended Projectors', body: '<p><strong>Best short-throw for golf:</strong> BenQ TH671ST ($599) — 0.69 throw ratio, 3,000 lumens, 1080p. The most popular simulator projector. See our <a href="/best-golf-simulator-projectors/">full projector review</a>.</p><p><strong>Best ultra-short-throw:</strong> BenQ V5000i ($1,699) — sits inches from the screen. Best for rooms under 10 feet deep.</p><p><strong>Best budget:</strong> Optoma GT1080HDRx ($549) — 0.50 throw ratio. Widest image from shortest distance.</p>' },
      { h2: 'Ceiling Mount vs Floor vs Shelf', body: '<p><strong>Ceiling mount</strong> is ideal — keeps the projector out of the swing path and provides the best image angle. Most short-throw projectors have keystone correction for angled mounting.</p><p><strong>Floor mount</strong> works but the projector may be in the swing path for tall golfers. Use a low shelf behind the hitting position.</p><p><strong>Shelf mount</strong> is the easiest DIY option. Mount a shelf on the back wall at 7 feet high and point the projector forward. Most simulators use this approach.</p>' },
    ],
    faq: [
      { q: 'How far should a projector be from a golf simulator screen?', a: 'Depends on throw ratio. Short-throw projectors (0.5-0.8): 4-8 feet. Standard projectors (1.0-2.0): 10-15 feet. Most garages need short-throw.' },
      { q: 'What throw ratio do I need for a golf simulator?', a: 'For most garages (12-15 ft deep): 0.5-0.8 throw ratio. For large dedicated rooms (15+ ft): standard 1.0-2.0 throw ratio works.' },
      { q: 'Can I use any projector for a golf simulator?', a: 'Yes, if the throw ratio fits your room. You need at least 3,000 lumens for a bright image, 1080p resolution minimum, and low input lag (under 30ms) for responsive ball flight.' },
    ],
    sources: [{ label: 'BenQ — Throw Ratio Calculator', url: 'https://www.benq.com/' }],
