    intro: `An iron fitting adjusts four key variables — shaft flex, club length, lie angle, and grip size — to match your unique swing. The result: 5-10 yards more distance, tighter dispersion, and irons that feel like they were made for you. But timing matters. Here is when fitting is worth it and when to skip it.`,
    toc: ['When to Get Fitted', 'What Gets Measured', 'Shaft Flex', 'Club Length and Lie Angle', 'Grip Size', 'How to Prepare'],
