    words: '1,800',
    category: 'improve-game',
    pageType: 'tutorial',
    tag: 'GUIDE',
    emoji: '🔧',
    datePublished: '2026-05-17',
    dateModified: '2026-05-13',
    title: 'Golf Shaft Flex Guide',
    titleDisplay: 'Golf Shaft Flex Guide — How to Choose the Right Flex for Your Swing',
    description: 'Golf shaft flex guide for 2026. Regular vs Stiff vs Senior explained with swing speed charts and recommendations.',
    excerpt: 'Wrong shaft flex costs you 5-10 yards and creates inconsistent ball flight. Here is how to choose the right flex for your swing.',
    bottomLine: 'Most male golfers should play Regular flex (75-90 mph driver speed). Stiff is for 90-105 mph. Senior for under 75 mph. Get measured with a launch monitor for certainty.',
    intro: `Shaft flex determines how much the club bends during your swing. The right flex maximizes energy transfer — wrong flex wastes speed or creates timing problems. Most golfers play the wrong flex because they overestimate their swing speed.`,
