    datePublished: '2026-06-06',
    dateModified: '2026-06-06',
    title: 'Best Golf Shirts — Polos That Breathe and Look Good',
    titleDisplay: 'Best Golf Shirts — Polos Tested in Midwest Heat',
    description: 'Best golf shirts and polos tested in summer heat. Nike, FootJoy, adidas, and Puma compared for breathability, fit, UV protection, and whether they hold up.',
    excerpt: 'Golf polos tested in 90-degree Midwest rounds — which ones breathe and which ones cling.',
    ogImage: 'https://www.cubicalgolfer.com/images/thumbnails/accessories-thumb.webp',
    thumbnail: '/images/thumbnails/golf-shirts-thumb.webp',
    bottomLine: 'The Nike Dri-FIT Victory delivers the best combination of breathability, fit, and value at $45. The FootJoy ProDry is the premium pick for golfers who want moisture management that genuinely works through 18 holes in humidity. After wearing all four through a full summer of Chicago golf, the Nike Dri-FIT Victory earned the most rotation time in my closet — it wicks, it fits, and at $45 it does not hurt to sweat through it.',
    intro: 'A bad golf shirt turns a hot round into a miserable one. The right polo wicks sweat, blocks UV, moves with your swing, and still looks presentable at the clubhouse after 18 holes. We tested four popular golf polos through summer rounds at South Shore and Harborside — two courses where Midwest humidity tests every fabric claim.\n\nEach polo worn for a minimum of 3 full walking rounds in temperatures ranging from 78°F to 94°F, then machine washed and assessed for shape retention, color fading, and continued wicking performance.\n\nIf you are also shopping for the rest of your on-course outfit, see our <a href="/best-golf-shorts/">golf shorts</a>, <a href="/best-golf-pants/">golf pants</a>, <a href="/best-golf-hats/">hats</a>, and <a href="/best-golf-sunglasses/">sunglasses</a> guides.\n\nLast updated: June 2026.',
    testingNotes: 'Each polo tested over 6-8 walking rounds across summer 2025. Temperatures ranged from 78°F to 94°F with humidity from 55-85%. Each polo machine washed 10-plus times (cold water, tumble dry low) and assessed for shrinkage, pilling, color retention, and continued moisture-wicking performance.',
    toc: ['What to Look For', 'Nike Dri-FIT Victory', 'FootJoy ProDry', 'adidas Ultimate365', 'Puma Cloudspun', 'Sizing Guide', 'FAQ'],
