    faq: [
      { q: 'Should I wear sunglasses while putting?', a: 'Most tour pros remove sunglasses to putt. For weekend golfers, leaving them on is fine as long as the lenses do not distort depth perception. Golf-specific lenses (Oakley Prizm Golf) are designed to be worn while putting — standard polarized lenses can flatten green contours and should be removed.' },
      { q: 'Are polarized sunglasses good for golf?', a: 'Polarized lenses reduce glare (good for bright conditions, water hazards) but can flatten the appearance of subtle green slopes (bad for reading putts). For most weekend golfers, the glare reduction benefit outweighs the green-reading downside. Serious putters should test both polarized and non-polarized before committing.' },
    ],
